Description: Digital photograph (colour); detail of painted rock art projecting from a rock shelter roof, showing eight human figures and three unidentified shapes infilled in light brown. The human figures are upright and all facing left but one on the top left, bent at the waist and facing right. To the lower left of this figure is a small stick figure style figure with bent knees, facing forward and down and to the right of this is a figure standing straight. Next right is an eroded foot pointing left and then the clearest figure of the tableau, an elongated figure with thin curved waist, full hips and legs. To the right of this are two smaller figures in the same orientation. At the centre is a large unidentified shape, possibly the remains of another figure and to the far left are two very faded linear shapes in light brown. Wadi Anak, Egypt. Scanned
Curator's comments: This site is a long, sloping shelter running up and under the protected side of an inselberg.
Acquisition name: Donated by: Trust for African Rock Art
